[♪♪♪]

01:14.320 --> 01:16.766
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:25.800 --> 01:28.167
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

01:47.280 --> 01:49.681
[♪♪♪]

02:01.520 --> 02:03.921
[LOW GRUNTING]

02:13.040 --> 02:14.041
[KEYS JINGLING]

02:14.200 --> 02:15.486
MAN 1:
Are you sure you have the right keys?

02:15.640 --> 02:17.005
MAN 2: Trust me, it's the right key.

02:17.160 --> 02:18.571
WOMAN: Okay, then, open the door.

02:18.720 --> 02:21.246
MAN 1:
It shouldn't be taking so long, man.

02:21.400 --> 02:22.811
[ALARM BEEPS]

02:22.960 --> 02:25.167
WOMAN: 20, 19, 18...

02:25.320 --> 02:27.084
ALEX: Rocky, those are very slow seconds.

02:27.240 --> 02:29.004
- MONEY: Yo, kill that already.
- WOMAN: ...17, 16...

02:29.160 --> 02:31.003
- MONEY: Dude, come on.
- ROCKY: ...15, 14, 13...

02:31.160 --> 02:33.242
[BEEPING CONTINUES THEN MONEY CHUCKLING]

02:33.400 --> 02:36.483
- MONEY: This is what I'm talking about.
- ROCKY: ...12, 11, 10, 9...

02:36.640 --> 02:38.404
[ALARM STOPS]

02:40.840 --> 02:42.763
I told you this was gonna be fancy.

02:45.120 --> 02:47.088
All right, so, just like last time.

02:47.240 --> 02:49.049
No cash.
The total take has to fall below ten G's.

02:49.200 --> 02:50.201
Yeah, yeah. Whatever, Judge Judy.

02:50.360 --> 02:51.486
- Come on.
- Let's do this.

02:53.760 --> 02:55.762
[♪♪♪]

03:14.760 --> 03:16.922
[LAUGHS]

03:19.840 --> 03:23.083
[SIGHS]

03:23.240 --> 03:24.651
ALEX: Okay, let's get out of here.

03:26.720 --> 03:28.245
[ALARM BEEPING]

03:28.440 --> 03:30.363
[ALARM WAILING]

03:42.200 --> 03:44.202
[♪♪♪]

04:00.560 --> 04:03.564
Hey, Rocky, did you hear
that Kopecky's moving away?

04:03.760 --> 04:05.649
Everybody's leaving.

04:07.920 --> 04:09.922
You know, if we keep hitting
houses like today's...

04:10.080 --> 04:11.127
Rocky, and...

04:11.280 --> 04:12.930
Bye-bye, Detroit.

04:13.080 --> 04:15.447
And hola, California.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.485
Wait, wait. You're going away, Rock?

04:19.640 --> 04:21.608
Yeah, as soon as I can.

04:23.880 --> 04:25.882
When are you, when are you coming back?

04:27.120 --> 04:28.360
Never.

04:29.640 --> 04:31.483
You should come with us.

04:31.640 --> 04:33.210
Uh...

04:33.360 --> 04:34.964
ROCKY: What?

04:35.120 --> 04:36.724
Everyone else is gone.

04:36.920 --> 04:39.002
I got my dad here.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.089
I'll miss you, then.

04:48.800 --> 04:50.768
[♪♪♪]

05:06.960 --> 05:08.962
Dad?

05:10.200 --> 05:12.282
You home?

05:29.480 --> 05:32.404
[♪♪♪]

05:49.560 --> 05:51.961
[♪♪♪]

05:58.320 --> 05:59.731
Yo, this is it, man?

05:59.920 --> 06:01.968
Minus my 40 percent.

06:02.120 --> 06:03.565
Take it or leave it.

06:03.720 --> 06:05.051
There's a fucking Rolex in there, bro.

06:05.200 --> 06:06.611
And what do you think...

06:06.800 --> 06:09.451
I'm going to put it up
for auction at Sotheby's? Heh.

06:12.960 --> 06:14.246
Do you know how much...

06:14.400 --> 06:16.528
people on the street pay for a hot Rolex?

06:16.680 --> 06:18.967
Heh. You want money?

06:19.120 --> 06:21.009
Then steal money.

06:21.160 --> 06:22.571
Fucking bullshit, bro.

06:23.800 --> 06:26.804
Do you want this new tip or not?

06:30.720 --> 06:32.290
MONEY: All right, let's hear it.

06:32.440 --> 06:34.966
MONEY: 1837 Buena Vista Street.

06:35.160 --> 06:38.285
House is with your dad's security company.
I already checked.

06:38.440 --> 06:41.284
Guy who owns it is an Army vet loner.

06:41.440 --> 06:42.805
No family.

06:43.000 --> 06:44.126
Just him in the house.

06:44.280 --> 06:46.926
That part of the city is a ghost town.
It looks like a dump.

06:47.080 --> 06:48.320
That's actually good news.

06:48.480 --> 06:49.811
How's that good news?

06:49.960 --> 06:51.291
The story goes...

06:51.440 --> 06:52.965
some preppy girl a few years ago...

06:53.120 --> 06:54.724
ran over this guy's daughter.

06:54.880 --> 06:56.769
- Jesus.
- The daughter dies...

06:56.920 --> 06:59.321
and this preppy, rich-ass family...

06:59.520 --> 07:01.204
pays him off...

07:01.360 --> 07:02.850
gives him a big-ass sediment.

07:03.000 --> 07:04.729
Settlement.

07:04.880 --> 07:06.370
Blow me, Your Honor.

07:06.520 --> 07:11.082
All right, this guy
is sitting on at least...

07:11.280 --> 07:13.442
300K.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.409
Boom!

07:15.560 --> 07:18.723
I mean, if I deliver
this stake to Raul, man...

07:18.880 --> 07:20.405
he will shit his pants.

07:20.560 --> 07:22.722
Do you think the money's in the house?

07:22.920 --> 07:25.002
I don't know. Let's go find out.

07:25.160 --> 07:26.491
Guys, no. We don't do cash.

07:26.640 --> 07:28.005
Above ten K, it's major larceny.

07:28.160 --> 07:29.571
That means ten years if we get caught.

07:29.760 --> 07:31.683
- We won't get caught.
- ALEX: Okay, and then what?

07:31.840 --> 07:33.444
That amount brings a serious cop presence.

07:33.640 --> 07:34.687
They'll do an investigation.

07:34.840 --> 07:35.887
My dad could get in trouble.

07:36.040 --> 07:37.326
I knew you'd bitch out, man.

07:37.480 --> 07:39.403
I just knew it.

07:39.600 --> 07:42.888
Alex, if we do this right,
we never have to do it again.

07:49.280 --> 07:51.282
Where are you going?

07:51.440 --> 07:54.171
We're not doing this one.

07:54.320 --> 07:56.607
Seriously?

07:56.760 --> 07:58.649
Give us the fucking keys, man.

07:58.800 --> 08:00.086
- We'll fucking do it.
- Alex!

08:06.480 --> 08:07.481
[PHONE BEEPS]

08:09.400 --> 08:11.402
[♪♪♪]

08:34.320 --> 08:37.688
"Gulf War veteran reaches
six-figure settlement."

08:38.960 --> 08:41.361
Six-figure settlement.

08:42.679 --> 08:43.885
All right.

08:51.760 --> 08:54.281
REPORTER [ON TV]: The suspect was
leaving the rear entrance of the club.

08:54.440 --> 08:56.522
Are you done, Diddy?

08:58.600 --> 09:00.204
Be a doll and get your mother...

09:00.360 --> 09:02.328
a large four-cheese from Tony's.

09:02.520 --> 09:03.521
[MICROWAVE BEEPS]

09:03.680 --> 09:05.762
- So Trevor's living here now?
- MOTHER: Don't be a bitch, Roxanne.

09:05.920 --> 09:07.684
It's just a few months
till he can find a new job.

09:07.840 --> 09:10.684
You have no money in here.

09:10.840 --> 09:12.968
MOTHER: You pay for it then.

09:14.280 --> 09:16.009
I know you're making money.

09:17.360 --> 09:20.330
[SIGHS]

09:20.480 --> 09:21.766
I'm done.

09:21.920 --> 09:24.207
Your lips look sore.

09:24.360 --> 09:26.647
That's how you're making
your cash out there?

09:26.800 --> 09:29.041
Ha, ha. Huh?

09:29.200 --> 09:30.929
[TREVOR CHUCKLES]

09:31.080 --> 09:33.048
Okay, Diddy, let's go for a walk.

09:35.560 --> 09:37.767
I want to go to the beach.

09:37.920 --> 09:41.129
Yeah, well, it's not summer, monkeyhead.

09:41.280 --> 09:43.567
I want to be a surfer.

09:43.720 --> 09:46.530
There's no surf in Michigan.

09:48.240 --> 09:52.165
- Not fair.
- Yeah, well...

09:52.360 --> 09:53.885
[SNIFFLES]

09:54.040 --> 09:56.122
some things you can't change, baby.

09:56.320 --> 09:57.367
[PHONE BUZZES]

09:57.520 --> 09:59.284
No matter how unfair they are.

09:59.440 --> 10:01.363
What a bummer.

10:04.880 --> 10:07.008
Hey, you know where there is surf?

10:09.120 --> 10:10.610
[WHISPERING] California.

10:10.760 --> 10:13.331
What do you say
you and I move there together?

10:13.480 --> 10:14.561
Would you like that?

10:14.720 --> 10:16.290
Okay.

10:16.440 --> 10:17.851
I promise then.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.287
[BOTH EXHALE]

10:27.720 --> 10:29.722
[♪♪♪]

10:36.440 --> 10:39.683
[BIRD SCREECHING]

11:05.400 --> 11:07.402
[♪♪♪]

11:31.400 --> 11:33.402
[SIGHS]

11:35.920 --> 11:37.445
Is that a new tattoo?

11:37.600 --> 11:38.681
Yeah.

11:38.880 --> 11:40.041
I got it last night.

11:40.240 --> 11:42.368
- ALEX: Is it a...?
- Ladybug.

11:43.560 --> 11:46.370
Why a ladybug?

11:49.680 --> 11:51.762
What?

11:53.760 --> 11:57.128
When my dad left,
my mom started drinking...

11:57.320 --> 11:59.607
and she told me that...

11:59.760 --> 12:02.525
my dad's leaving was all my fault.

12:05.160 --> 12:08.289
And I missed him a lot, so I'd cry.

12:09.480 --> 12:11.482
She got so fed up with the crying...

12:11.640 --> 12:14.166
that she would lock me
in the trunk of her car.

12:14.320 --> 12:16.721
Sometimes for hours.

12:18.280 --> 12:20.169
But there was this, um...

12:22.200 --> 12:24.282
A little hole in the trunk...

12:24.440 --> 12:26.249
and one time a ladybug flew in...

12:26.400 --> 12:29.165
kept me company.

12:29.320 --> 12:31.163
It made me feel safe.

12:33.880 --> 12:36.121
When I reach California,
I'm gonna color this tat...

12:36.280 --> 12:38.726
and that's the last time
I will mark my body.

12:45.840 --> 12:48.969
If we get this money,
I'm going away with you guys.

12:52.200 --> 12:54.487
I know you will.

12:54.640 --> 12:57.405
[FOOTSTEPS THEN DOOR OPENS]

13:00.000 --> 13:03.129
At least four blocks around,
houses aren't occupied.

13:04.600 --> 13:06.967
No people means no Five-0 on patrol.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.531
It's gonna be a piece of cake.

13:08.720 --> 13:10.290
The guy's a shut-in...

13:10.440 --> 13:12.124
hasn't left his house in, like, five days.

13:12.280 --> 13:13.725
I say we do it with him in the house.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.325
I'll get a chloro-bomb.

13:15.520 --> 13:16.646
[BARKING]

13:16.800 --> 13:17.961
ROCKY: Oh, shit!

13:18.120 --> 13:19.360
- Jesus.
- Fucking A.

13:19.520 --> 13:20.726
Get off my fucking car, dog shit!

13:20.880 --> 13:23.724
[BARKING CONTINUES]

13:25.520 --> 13:27.090
[MAN WHISTLES]

13:27.280 --> 13:29.248
[BARKING FADES]

13:29.400 --> 13:31.004
Shit, that's our guy.

13:33.560 --> 13:35.562
[♪♪♪]

13:39.400 --> 13:40.970
Wait, is he blind?

13:41.120 --> 13:44.363
MONEY:
He lost his sight in Iraq or something.

13:44.520 --> 13:46.921
That's kind of fucked up
to rob a blind guy, isn't it?

13:47.080 --> 13:49.287
Just because he's blind don't
mean he's a fucking saint, bro.

13:49.440 --> 13:51.886
[SIGHS]

13:52.040 --> 13:53.041
We do this tonight.

13:53.200 --> 13:54.281
[ENGINE STARTS]

14:07.640 --> 14:09.449
[♪♪♪]

14:09.600 --> 14:11.967
[DISTANT BARKING]

14:18.560 --> 14:20.642
ALEX: The whole neighborhood
is fucking empty.

14:20.800 --> 14:23.280
This guy's the last man standing.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.081
MONEY: The lights are out.

14:28.240 --> 14:29.241
He must be asleep.

14:29.400 --> 14:31.209
He's blind.

14:31.360 --> 14:32.771
Lights off doesn't mean anything.

14:32.920 --> 14:33.967
ROCKY: It's 2 a.m.

14:34.120 --> 14:36.771
He's sleeping.

14:36.920 --> 14:38.763
Let's take care of that dog first, yeah?

14:46.720 --> 14:48.722
[BARKING CONTINUES]

15:00.400 --> 15:02.687
[DOG BARKING]

15:02.880 --> 15:05.531
MONEY: Come on, man.

15:05.680 --> 15:08.081
[BARKING CONTINUES]

15:15.400 --> 15:16.561
He's chewing it.

15:16.720 --> 15:18.085
It'll be lights out in a sec.

15:18.240 --> 15:20.208
[DOG GROANING]

15:25.000 --> 15:27.401
There's four locks.
You got the other keys?

15:27.560 --> 15:29.528
- I only have the one.
- Ah. Fuck me.

15:31.760 --> 15:34.127
Why wouldn't he give backup
keys to the security company?

15:34.280 --> 15:35.645
Because the money's in there...

15:35.800 --> 15:38.485
and the paranoid fuck
doesn't trust nobody.

15:38.640 --> 15:40.404
ROCKY: Let's check for a side door.

15:48.680 --> 15:50.523
[GRUNTS]

16:07.080 --> 16:09.128
[SNORING SOFTLY]

16:11.080 --> 16:12.923
[WHISTLING SOFTLY]

16:16.880 --> 16:18.450
Sweet dreams, pup.

16:42.360 --> 16:43.521
What's that?

16:43.680 --> 16:45.011
We just have to point this
in the general direction...

16:45.160 --> 16:46.321
of the master keypad,
and it'll kill the alarm.

16:46.520 --> 16:49.364
Okay, open the fucking door, Dexter.

16:53.240 --> 16:55.402
ALEX: Yes. Got it.

16:55.560 --> 16:56.641
Shit.

16:56.800 --> 16:58.040
ROCKY: What's wrong?

16:58.240 --> 16:59.446
It won't open.

17:08.920 --> 17:10.126
[GRUNTS]

17:10.440 --> 17:13.125
MONEY: This guy isn't messing around.

17:14.760 --> 17:16.046
There's a bolt here.

17:16.200 --> 17:17.929
I can feel it.

17:18.079 --> 17:19.605
- Come on.
- ALEX: That's too loud.

17:19.760 --> 17:21.683
- That's too loud.
- Fucking stop.

17:24.800 --> 17:25.925
What about that window?

17:27.079 --> 17:28.127
There's no bars on it.

17:28.280 --> 17:29.520
- I can fit in there.
- ALEX: What?

17:29.680 --> 17:31.762
No, we're not sending you in there alone.

17:32.960 --> 17:34.485
Nobody's sending me anywhere.

17:34.640 --> 17:36.642
I'm going myself.

17:39.400 --> 17:40.811
Help me up.

17:40.960 --> 17:42.121
ALEX: Here, Rocky.

17:42.280 --> 17:43.281
You only got 30 seconds.

17:43.440 --> 17:44.441
ROCKY: Okay.

17:44.600 --> 17:46.329
MONEY: Here. Come here.

18:03.160 --> 18:05.162
[♪♪♪]

18:17.000 --> 18:18.525
[CHIRPS]

18:18.680 --> 18:20.887
[BEEPING STEADILY]

18:25.040 --> 18:27.441
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

18:36.280 --> 18:39.090
[GLASS CRUNCHING]

18:44.560 --> 18:46.881
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

18:50.160 --> 18:52.481
[BEEPING INCREASES]

18:59.520 --> 19:02.967
[CHIRPING THEN BEEPING STOPS]

19:03.160 --> 19:05.447
[PANTING]

19:26.200 --> 19:28.646
[PANTING CONTINUES]

19:32.320 --> 19:34.368
[♪♪♪]

19:50.080 --> 19:51.445
MONEY: Slow your roll, fool.

19:51.600 --> 19:53.728
She must have got it by now. She's fine.

19:55.640 --> 19:57.051
Yeah, like you really give a fuck.

19:57.200 --> 19:58.850
What'd you say?

19:59.000 --> 20:01.162
That's my bitch in there.

20:01.320 --> 20:03.243
Of course I give a fuck.

20:03.400 --> 20:05.607
Let me give you some advice.

20:05.760 --> 20:07.205
Be a good friend...

20:07.360 --> 20:10.125
and stay in the fucking
friend zone, all right?

20:11.640 --> 20:13.881
[CREAKS]

20:14.040 --> 20:15.121
Are you okay?

20:15.280 --> 20:16.566
Yes.

20:16.720 --> 20:18.484
Shoes off.

20:21.040 --> 20:23.042
[♪♪♪]

20:54.080 --> 20:56.401
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS THEN GASPING]

21:02.040 --> 21:03.565
[SCOFFS]

21:03.720 --> 21:05.404
- What the fuck?
- Hey.

21:24.640 --> 21:26.847
[DOOR CREAKS]

21:44.520 --> 21:46.329
[SIGHS]

21:53.520 --> 21:55.761
MONEY: Hey. Hey.

21:55.960 --> 21:57.724
ALEX: Okay.

22:10.560 --> 22:12.130
[FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

22:15.640 --> 22:17.722
GIRL [SINGING ON TV]: ♪ I love you ♪

22:17.880 --> 22:20.804
♪ Yes, I'll be your valentine ♪

22:20.960 --> 22:24.328
♪ Valentine, valentine ♪

22:24.480 --> 22:27.529
♪ Yes, I'll be your valentine ♪

22:27.680 --> 22:30.365
♪ I love you ♪

22:34.960 --> 22:36.564
Just three seeds, right?

22:36.720 --> 22:39.121
Just three?

22:39.280 --> 22:42.011
One, two...

22:42.160 --> 22:45.130
and three.

22:45.280 --> 22:48.762
Put three seeds in there...

22:48.920 --> 22:51.048
and the cup is all empty.

22:53.440 --> 22:55.761
Now you water it?

22:55.920 --> 22:58.082
Okay, now we water it.

22:58.240 --> 23:00.766
Okay, Mom.

23:00.920 --> 23:03.287
Then it takes the water.

23:11.720 --> 23:13.563
Just three seeds.

23:13.720 --> 23:15.563
WOMAN: What are you doing?

23:15.720 --> 23:17.370
GIRL: Planting a tree.

23:19.560 --> 23:22.882
WOMAN: How big is the tree going to get?

23:23.040 --> 23:25.008
GIRL: As big as the sky!

23:25.160 --> 23:26.571
WOMAN: Wow.

23:26.720 --> 23:30.327
[DOOR CREAKS]

23:32.240 --> 23:33.890
What does a tree need to grow?

23:34.040 --> 23:37.203
GIRL: Water, seeds, soil...

23:37.360 --> 23:39.203
and sun.

23:39.360 --> 23:42.170
WOMAN: Sounds good.

23:53.240 --> 23:54.241
[GASPS]

23:54.400 --> 23:55.561
GIRL [SINGING ON TV]:
♪ Yes, I'll be your valentine ♪

23:55.720 --> 23:58.690
♪ Valentine, valentine ♪

23:58.840 --> 24:01.810
♪ Yes, I'll be your valentine ♪

24:02.000 --> 24:03.650
♪ I love you ♪♪

24:08.320 --> 24:10.084
Then it will grow.

24:13.440 --> 24:15.568
Mom, can I have more water?

24:20.160 --> 24:22.128
[GROANS]

24:43.480 --> 24:46.051
[DOOR CREAKS]

24:51.200 --> 24:52.201
Done!

24:52.360 --> 24:54.124
[GASPS]

24:54.280 --> 24:55.281
ALEX: What the fuck, dude?

24:55.440 --> 24:56.521
MONEY: The guy's gassed out.

24:56.720 --> 24:57.846
He's out.

24:58.000 --> 24:59.001
He's in Sleeping Beauty mode.

24:59.160 --> 25:00.924
- It's fine.
- Guys.

25:05.640 --> 25:06.846
That's a big-ass lock.

25:07.000 --> 25:09.002
ROCKY: If the money's in the house...

25:09.160 --> 25:11.970
probably in there.

25:12.120 --> 25:14.088
ALEX: You think you can crack it open?

25:14.280 --> 25:15.770
MONEY: Yeah, I got this.

25:18.280 --> 25:20.282
[WOOD CREAKING]

25:20.440 --> 25:21.487
[MONEY GRUNTING]

25:25.600 --> 25:26.965
Fuck.

25:27.120 --> 25:30.727
[GRUNTING CONTINUES]

25:30.920 --> 25:32.490
ROCKY: Jesus.

25:32.640 --> 25:34.529
[PANTING]

25:34.720 --> 25:35.881
Do you have anything else?

25:36.040 --> 25:37.405
Yeah.

25:37.560 --> 25:38.766
Yeah, yeah.

25:38.920 --> 25:41.287
I've got a more powerful tool.

25:43.040 --> 25:44.530
What the hell is that?

25:44.680 --> 25:46.205
It's a nine millimeter Beretta.

25:46.360 --> 25:48.442
Gangster-style, bitches.

25:48.600 --> 25:49.965
Why did you bring a gun?

25:50.120 --> 25:51.929
This is a soldier's house, Alex.

25:52.080 --> 25:53.570
Like I'm gonna come in here
without some chrome.

25:53.720 --> 25:56.610
ROCKY:
Money, you've never shot a gun before.

25:56.760 --> 25:58.888
Yeah, well, it's time
to pop that cherry, baby.

25:59.040 --> 26:00.804
Because I'm going to pop that
shit like a fucking tuna can.

26:00.960 --> 26:03.641
ALEX: Do you have any idea what
bringing a gun to a burglary means?

26:03.800 --> 26:05.290
Yeah, it gives me...

